Name: mild pre-eclampsia
Definition: A pre-eclampsia characterized by the presence of hypertension without evidence of end-organ damage

Name: severe pre-eclampsia
Definition: A pre-eclampsia that has_symptom at least one of the following

Name: obsolete HIV wasting syndrome
Definition: An acquired immunodeficiency syndrome that results_in involuntary loss of more than 10% of body weight
Synonym: Human immunodeficiency virus infection wasting syndrome

Name: eclampsia
Definition: A pre-eclampsia characterized by the presence of seizures.
